The paper deals with the information-theoretic capacity scaling of wireless ad hoc networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which is concerned with the fundamental limits of communication and data processing. The paper uses an exact channel model from Maxwell's equations, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.PHYS (Physics and Society). The paper proposes a modified hierarchical cooperation for achieving capacity, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper deals with wireless networks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a lower bound on the capacity of multiple-input multiple-output channel, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
